143.speaker: LADY
143.character: ご注文　お決まりですか？
143.definition: Are you ready to order? A polar bear?!

144.speaker: KIRINO
144.character: そ…　それじゃ 自己紹介から始めましょうか
144.definition: H-How about we start with introductions?

147.speaker: KIRINO
147.character: 動物園の飼育員をやっています
147.definition: I'm a zoo keeper. Nice to meet you.

149.speaker: HANDA
149.character: は…　は…　半田です！

150.speaker: HANDA
150.character: 本日は　このように 晴れがましい合コンに　お…　お招きいただき
150.definition: I-I humbly t-thank you f-for i-inviting me to this f-formal group blind date today.

151.speaker: HANDA
151.character: ふつつか者ではありますが
151.definition: I am quite inexperienced in this venture,

152.character: 以後　よろしく お見知りおきください
152.definition: but I'm pleased to make your acquaintance.

154.speaker: KIRINO
154.character: そこまで丁寧な 自己紹介じゃなくて大丈夫です
154.definition: Your introduction doesn't have to be that formal.

155.speaker: HANDA
155.character: けど　初対面だから
155.definition: But this is the first time I'm meeting them.

157.speaker: KIRINO
157.character: 合コンって　そういう感じのものじゃないんで
157.definition: Group blind dates aren't that formal.

158.speaker: HANDA
158.character: 続きまして 私と同じ職場に勤める
158.definition: In addition, please allow me to introduce you to Panda,

159.character: パンダくんを紹介します！

160.speaker: KIRINO
160.character: だから　かたいって…

161.speaker: KIRINO
161.character: すみません パンダ　連れてきちゃって
161.definition: I'm sorry, we brought a panda.

163.speaker: GIRLS
163.definition: So cute! They don't seem to mind Panda being here. And then we have...

164.speaker: POLAR BEAR
164.character: シロクマです ふだんは　カフェやってます
164.definition: I'm Polar Bear. I run a café.

167.speaker: GIRL
167.definition: I want to go! What's it called?

168.speaker: POLAR BEAR
168.definition: Polar Bear's Café. So straight to the point.

169.speaker: GIRL
169.character: あの　もしかして 雑誌とかに載ってないですか？
169.definition: By any chance, was it featured in any magazines?

171.speaker: GIRL
171.character: すごい！　見たことある
171.definition: Wow! I've totally seen it before!

172.speaker: GIRL
172.character: 今度　行ってもいいですか？
172.definition: Is it okay if we stop by sometime?

175.speaker: POLAR BEAR
175.character: 趣味は　アザラシの捕獲

177.speaker: GIRL
177.character: 今度連れてってください
177.definition: Can you take us with you next time?

178.speaker: KIRINO
178.definition: I don't think that's a good idea.

179.speaker: GIRL
179.character: じゃあ　女子 いきますね

181.speaker: KIRINO
181.character: 先輩　ヒロミちゃん

186.speaker: HANDA
186.character: わかってるよ　大丈夫 聞こえるから
186.definition: I know, I can hear them just fine. Go ahead with your order. Let's start off with draft beers.

188.speaker: PANDA
188.definition: Let's start off with bamboo. Bamboo?

189.character: ちょっと 置いてないんですが…
189.definition: I'm sorry, we don't carry that...

190.speaker: PANDA
190.character: え～っ　じゃあ　笹
190.definition: Really? Then how about bamboo grass?

191.speaker: LADY
191.character: 笹も　ないんですが…

192.speaker: PANDA
192.character: じゃあ　みんな　どうしてるの？
192.definition: Then what do you usually order?

196.speaker: POLAR BEAR
196.character: とりあえず　アザラシ

198.speaker: POLAR BEAR
198.definition: Can I bring some from home?

199.speaker: KIRINO
199.definition: No. Let's just start with six draft beers and one juice.

201.speaker: GIRL
201.character: そうよね　パンダっていったら やっぱり竹よね
201.definition: I guess that makes sense, he is a panda after all.

202.speaker: GIRL
202.character: 食べてるとこ　見てみたい
202.definition: I totally want to see him eat it.

203.speaker: GIRL
203.definition: That'd be so cute! You should totally eat bamboo!

204.speaker: KIRINO
204.character: 何なんだ？　この合コン…
204.definition: What kind of group blind date is this?

205.speaker: PENGUIN
205.character: いや　僕はね　合コンに行きたいって言ってるわけじゃないんだよ
205.definition: I'm not saying that I want to go to the group blind date.

207.speaker: PENGUIN
207.character: ただね　僕がずっとパンダくんの話を聞いていたわけだからさ
207.definition: It's just I was the one listening to Panda's story that whole time,

208.speaker: PENGUIN
208.character: 誘うなら　僕を誘うでしょ？
208.definition: so wouldn't it be natural for him to ask me?

209.speaker: PENGUIN
209.character: 僕にはペン子さんとい ペンギンがいるわけだから
209.definition: I have a penguin named Penko so I don't really want to go, but perhaps to study social activities...

211.speaker: PENGUIN
211.character: だから行きたくないよ
211.definition: I just told you that I didn't want to go.

212.speaker: PENGUIN
212.character: 笹子さんも　笹子さんでしょ
212.definition: Come on, Miss Sasako. If he was going to invite someone,he should've invited me instead of Polar Bear.

215.speaker: PENGUIN
215.definition: Of course I did. Argh! I bet everyone is having tons of fun right about now!

216.speaker: PENGUIN
216.character: 笹子さん カフェモカおかわり
216.definition: Could I get another café mocha, Miss Sasako? Yes. So you're all friends from college?

218.speaker: GIRL
218.character: そうそう　動物園にカピバラいますか？
218.definition: Oh, do you have any capybaras at your zoo?

219.speaker: GIRL
219.character: 今　流行ってますよね

220.speaker: GIRL
220.character: カピバラはネズミだってホントですか？
220.definition: Is a capybara really a rodent?

221.speaker: GIRL
221.character: じゃあ　動物園にはカピバラの温泉とか あるんですか？
221.definition: Then is there a capybara hot spring at the zoo? You should use your voice to answer, you know.

222.speaker: KIRINO
222.character: っていうか　さっきから何も　しゃべって ないじゃないですか
222.definition: Not to mention you haven't said a word for a while now.

224.speaker: KIRINO
224.character: 何か用事あるんですか？

225.speaker: HANDA
225.character: いや　風呂の掃除があるから
225.definition: I have to clean the bathroom.

226.speaker: KIRINO
226.character: わぁ～　ちょっと半田さん！

227.speaker: KIRINO
227.character: 風呂の掃除で帰るとか
227.definition: You totally can't say something like that in front of girls!

228.speaker: GIRL
228.definition: Is something wrong? E-Everything is fine. Sorry, he's a little drunk.

229.speaker: GIRL
229.character: 掃除がどうかしたんですか？
229.definition: Did he say something about cleaning {\i1}(souji){\i0}?

230.speaker: KIRINO
230.character: ソ…　ソーセージ注文しようかって 先輩が
230.definition: H-He said we should order some sausage {\i1}(so-se-ji){\i0}!

231.speaker: KIRINO
231.character: ねっ　先輩　僕注文しますね
231.definition: Right? I'll order some right now.

232.speaker: POLAR BEAR
232.character: ソーセージ盛り合わせ２つ

233.speaker: POLAR BEAR
233.character: お刺身　盛り合わせも

234.speaker: KIRINO
234.character: シロクマさん　すみません

235.speaker: KIRINO
235.character: あれ？　パンダくんは？

238.character: わざわざ取りに行ったの？
238.definition: You actually went to get some?

239.speaker: PANDA
239.character: だって　ここ　何もないんだもん
239.definition: Yeah, because they don't have anything here.

240.speaker: KIRINO
240.character: あるでしょ　いろいろ！

241.speaker: KIRINO
241.character: ナッツとか小エビの唐揚げとか
241.definition: See, like nuts and fried shrimp!

244.speaker: GIRL
244.character: パンダが竹食べてるとこ初めて見た！
244.definition: I've never seen a panda eat bamboo before!

246.speaker: GIRL
246.character: 写メ　撮っていいですか？

248.speaker: KIRINO
248.character: 持ち込みはダメだって書いてあるよ
248.definition: It says right here you can't bring outside food or drink.

251.speaker: LADY
251.definition: Here you go... Over here, over here!

252.speaker: KIRINO
252.character: すみません　持ち込みはダメだって 言ったんですけど
252.definition: I'm sorry, I told him he can't bring that in here.

253.speaker: LADY
253.definition: So... So cute! Can I take a picture, too?

254.speaker: KIRINO
254.definition: Um... what about not bringing in outside...

255.speaker: LADY
255.character: いいです　いいです！

256.speaker: GIRL
256.character: 半田さんは何の動物の飼育を しているんですか？
256.definition: What animal do you take care of, Mr. Handa? P-Pandas.

257.speaker: GIRLS
257.character: パンダ！？ パンダの飼育をしてるんですか？
257.definition: Pandas?! You take care of pandas?!

261.speaker: GIRL
261.character: パンダの話 いろいろ　聞かせてください！
261.definition: Tell us more about the pandas!

263.speaker: GIRLS
263.character: キャーッ！　かわいい！！

265.speaker: GIRLS
265.character: キャーッ！　かわいい！！

266.speaker: HANDA
266.character: ダラダラしているところ

267.speaker: GIRLS
267.character: キャーッ！　かわいい！！

268.speaker: GIRL
268.character: よく　見分けがつきますね
268.definition: I'm surprised you can tell them all apart.

271.speaker: GIRL
271.character: もっと聞かせてください！

272.speaker: HANDA
272.character: パンダは腸が短くて　竹からだと あまり栄養がとれないんです
272.definition: Pandas have short intestines and can't get much nutrition from bamboo.

273.speaker: HANDA
273.character: だから量で補うために１日中竹を食べているんです
273.definition: That's why they're eating bamboo all day. Wow, their intestines are short!

276.speaker: PANDA
276.character: 半田さん　もっと教えてあげて 僕のかわいいとこ
276.definition: Tell them even more cute things about me, Mr. Handa.

277.speaker: HANDA
277.character: 竹しか食べてないから
277.definition: Since they only eat bamboo, pandas' poop smells good.

278.speaker: HANDA
278.character: ちょっと レモンのにおいに似ているんです

279.speaker: HANDA
279.character: あぁ…　これ　これ

280.speaker: HANDA
280.character: うん　パンダのウンチのにおいです
280.definition: Yes, it smells like panda poop. Here, try it.

281.speaker: KIRINO
281.character: 先輩！　その情報は いらないんじゃないですか？
281.definition: Mr. Handa! I don't think they need that information.

282.speaker: PANDA
282.character: もう！　もっと かわいいエピソードにしてよ
282.definition: Come on, tell them something cuter than that.

283.speaker: HANDA
283.definition: Oh, really? Pandas look cute with their droopy eyes, right?

284.speaker: HANDA
284.character: あれって　実際の目は 小さくて　鋭いんですよ
284.definition: In actuality, their actual eye is small and very sharp. They don't need to know that either.

285.speaker: HANDA
285.definition: Really? I think that's really cute.

287.speaker: SASAKO
287.character: ペンギンさん　カフェモカ　おかわり お待たせしました
287.definition: Mr. Penguin, here you go, your refill on the café mocha.

289.speaker: GIRL
289.character: 今度　パンダコーナー 遊びにいってもいいですか？
289.definition: Is it okay if we come by the panda corner sometime?

290.speaker: HANDA
290.character: もちろんです　見にきてください
290.definition: Of course. Please come. I'll introduce you to Mr. Full-time Panda, too.

291.speaker: GIRL
291.character: 常勤パンダさん？ このパンダさんは何なんですか？
291.definition: Mr. Full-time Panda? So what's this panda, then?

292.speaker: HANDA
292.definition: He's a part-time panda that works two days a week.

293.speaker: GIRL
293.character: へぇ～　アルバイトなんだ？

300.speaker: PENGUIN
300.character: どうも　こんばんは

302.speaker: PANDA
302.character: 忙しいんじゃなかったの？ ペンギンさん

306.speaker: PENGUIN
306.definition: Ma-Ma-halo! Yay! Yay! Yay! Yay! Mr. Penguin, could I have the mic now?

307.speaker: PENGUIN
307.definition: I'm singing one more song! One more song!

310.speaker: KIRINO
310.definition: He's asleep! Wake up, Panda. Wake up!

313.speaker: GIRL
313.character: ねぇ　なんか似てない？

314.speaker: PENGUIN
314.character: このカフェにたどり着いた ラッキーボーイズ　アンド　ガールズ
314.definition: You lucky boys and girls who found this café

315.speaker: GIRL
315.character: 今日は　ありがとうございました
315.definition: Thank you very much for today.

316.speaker: GIRL
316.definition: It was a lot of fun!

317.speaker: GIRL
317.character: また　パンダの話聞かせてください
317.definition: Tell us more about pandas next time! Sure. Please visit the zoo.

318.speaker: GIRLS
318.character: はい じゃあ　おやすみなさい

319.speaker: HANDA
319.character: それじゃ　俺も 風呂の掃除あるから　帰るわ
319.definition: Okay, I have to go clean my bathroom, so I'm heading off.

323.speaker: POLAR BEAR
323.character: うちで　コーヒーでも飲んでく？
323.definition: Did you want to have some coffee at my place?

324.speaker: KIRINO
324.character: はい　シロクマさん

327.speaker: PENGUIN
327.character: あっ！　あれ？　みんなは？
